      • extractStringValue

        public static String extractStringValue(ResizableMemoryStructure struct,
                                        long preLen,
                                        long len)
        Extracts a "packed" string value from the structure. For this use, "packed" means that the string data is exactly as long as len, with no null terminator or WORD-size padding.
        Parameters:
        struct - the structure to extract from
        preLen - the number of bytes before the value to extract
        len - the size of the stored value
        Returns:
        the extracted string value

      • extractStringValueWordPadded

        public static String extractStringValueWordPadded(ResizableMemoryStructure struct,
                                                  long preLen,
                                                  long len)
        Extracts a "padded" string value from the structure. For this use, "padded" means that:
        • The string is not null-terminated
        • If the length of the string is odd, there is another packing null value at the end
        Parameters:
        struct - the structure to extract from
        preLen - the number of bytes before the value to extract
        len - the size of the stored value
        Returns:
        the extracted string value

      • extractStringValueUnpacked

        public static String extractStringValueUnpacked(ResizableMemoryStructure struct,
                                                long preLen,
                                                long len)
        Extracts an "unpacked" string value from the structure. For this use, "unpacked" means that:
        • The string is null-terminated
        • If the length of the string plus its terminator is odd, there is another packing null value at the end
        Parameters:
        struct - the structure to extract from
        preLen - the number of bytes before the value to extract
        len - the size of the stored value
        Returns:
        the extracted string value

      • writeStringValueWordPadded

        public static <T extends ResizableMemoryStructure> T writeStringValueWordPadded(T struct,
                                                                                int preLen,
                                                                                int currentLen,
                                                                                String value,
                                                                                IntConsumer sizeWriter)
        Writes a "padded" string value to the provided structure, using the provided IntConsumer to update an associated length value. For this use, "unpacked" means that:
        • The string is not null-terminated
        • If the length of the string plus its terminator is odd, there is another packing null value at the end
        Type Parameters:
        T - the class of the structure
        Parameters:
        struct - the structure to modify
        preLen - the amount of variable data in bytes before the place to write
        currentLen - the current length of the variable data to overwrite
        value - the value to write
        sizeWriter - a callback to modify an associated length field, if applicable
        Returns:
        the provided structure
